UPDATE: Wharf Road closed after car crashes
Updated 12:26pm Tuesday 3rd May 2016 in
By Stephen Davy-Osborne, Reporter
POLICE closed a road near Wroughton while a large crane retrieved a crashed car.
Royal Wootton Bassett and Cricklade Neighbourhood Police Team announced the road was closed shortly after 10.30am.
A large crane retrieveda red Hyundai that left the road.
A police spokesman said: "Due to the HIAB [crane]needing to extend its legs for the safe recovery the road will be closed for at least 30 minutes."
The road was reopened just after 11.30am.
